displayName: City of Campus, Grassland - Residential House

parameters:
Village Girl Shino: It's quite a spacious house, isn't it?
It feels even more so since my father passed away.
Clea: There's no one here... Nora, do you sense anything?

Thief Nora: No, I don't sense anything. I think there's no
one here!

Mage Relm: So, as Stolge-san said, stealing this genius's
time is the greatest sin!

Priestess Sophia: If that's the case, could it be that
searching for the person who submitted the request will be
our next job?
Clea: First, let's report to Stolge-san--

Hmm... That's troublesome. We haven't even finished
welcoming them.
Thief Perno: Long time no see, diligent adventurer
Clea: Is this a continuation of what happened back then?

Nora: T-This is strange! They should be here, but there's no
presence at all!

Thief Perno: Hehehe, would you mind lowering your weapons? I
have no intention of fighting, I simply want to talk as the
client.
Clea: I can't participate in stealing.

Thief Perno: It's the opposite, I want to return all the
stolen goods.
Thief Perno: My request is to put an end to Thief Perno.

Thief Perno: When my father died, I found a diary. In it,
there were records of thefts committed as Thief Perno.

Thief Perno: Putting an end to Thief Perno, who I learned
for the first time was my family, is my father's dying wish.
Thief Nora: Can't you just stop on your own?

Thief Perno: I can't easily quit due to the many
restrictions imposed by those rules.

Thief Perno: Returning all stolen goods. This is the only
way I can quit being Thief Perno.

Thief Perno: I requested your cooperation in returning the
stolen goods for that reason.

Thief Perno: I wonder if you would accept my request. It's
not just from me, but also from the family who wants to quit
being thieves.

Clea: Alright, I will believe in your words and accept the
request.

Priestess Sophia: Oh my, I wonder if Stolge-san will get
angry with me~?

Thief Perno: There was no mistake in my eyes... I will post
the first request on the campus bulletin board.
Clea: Is it possible for me to see the face of the client?

Thief Perno: I want to quit being Thief Perno, but I also
have the pride of our family, who has upheld the secret of
being thieves.

Thief Perno: That's why I can't reveal my true face. From
now on, please take care of me, Clea-san.
Clea: Let's go report to Stolge-san at the tavern.

Phoni the Phantom Thief: You noticed something strange and
came to check on me, huh? I'm really glad to have met such
good girls... but you see,
Phantom Thief Perno: I didn't want you to come if possible.

Phantom Thief Perno: The voice of someone who has been
hearing about the existence of the Phantom Thief Perno,
which has been continuing for a long time...

Phantom Thief Perno: It seems that the symbol mask was the
Phantom Thief Perno itself... That's why I... [I] quit being
a priest and became a thief...

First Generation Phantom Thief Perno: I have become the
Phantom Thief Perno! I won't let you interfere, the Phantom
Thief Perno will not end!

Clea: I'm not sure, but if we defeat the mask, will we be
able to save Perno-san?

Thief Nora: Are you planning to defeat Perno-san in order to
save her!?

Mage Relm: The source of magic power is the mask! So if we
defeat the mask, her body should be freed!

Priestess Sophia: If what she's saying is true, the first
generation Phantom Thief Perno has been using her family to
continue her thieving.

Priestess Sophia: It seems like a good idea to think that
way.

Clea: I'm not sure, but I will help Perno-san, who is the
client.

Phantom Thief Perno: Thank you again... I am now convinced
that the Phantom Thief Perno has come to an end.

Phantom Thief Perno: My family was being manipulated by the
first generation Phantom Thief Perno... It's ironic, isn't
it? The pride of my family became its downfall.

Phantom Thief Perno: With this, I can finally report to my
father. I'm really grateful to have been able to end it with
such reliable people.

Phantom Thief Perno: And now, this is the ritual to bid a
complete farewell to the last magical Phantom Thief Perno...

I still can't reveal my true identity. This is the pride I
inherited as a member of my family.
Goodbye, I'm really glad I could meet all of you.

???: Let's meet again in the darkness of the night
someday...

Housewife Shino: I immediately hit it off with my husband
and got married. We spend peaceful and ordinary days in a
nice place... I'm happy.
Thief Nora: Oh, you mustn't get up!

Master Thief Perno: Hehe, thank you for your concern, but
there's something important I need to talk about...

Master Thief Perno: Magic has been becoming unstable. This
is the [Voice] that keeps me going as a master thief.

Mage Relm: What exactly do you mean by [Voice]? It sounds
like something that actually exists!

Master Thief Perno: I don't understand it either... but I
can definitely hear it, I can definitely feel it.

Master Thief Perno: That voice gives me strength, but at the
same time, it keeps demanding that I remain as the Master
Thief Perno.

Priestess Sophia: By the way, speaking of which, there was
talk about my father at the tavern.

Master Thief Perno: My father also tried to quit being a
master thief. This is detailed in his diary, which is now an
heirloom.

Master Thief Perno: To be precise, although many members of
the clan tried to quit, it seems they couldn't break through
numerous rules.

Master Thief Perno: My father was no exception... He was
also driven by the [Voice] just like I am now.

Master Thief Perno: That's why I decided to rely on allies.
Master Thief Perno cannot quit on my own.

Clea: Please rest assured, I will never betray you as long
as you are a sincere client.

Mage Relm: Hmm, it seems like magic is intricately
involved... It's almost as if the concept of being bound by
a contract applies here.

Thief Nora: If you can use such amazing magic, it would be a
bit of a waste to quit, don't you think?

Master Thief Perno: I want to live a normal life, to live
normally, to play normally, to fall in love normally...

Master Thief Perno: I want to get married! Despite how I may
look, I'm actually at a decent age!

Master Thief Perno: That's why I will definitely quit being
a master thief! I will absolutely seize that thing called
normal happiness!

Clea: I may not be able to provide a marriage partner, but I
will accompany you until the end.

Master Thief Perno: Hehe, I've really met some good girls.
Just two more left... Next, I'll make a request to [Valt].

Master Thief Perno: Let's meet in the next request, shall
we?
Phantom Thief Perno: ...I've calmed down a bit.

Phantom Thief Perno: Thank you so much, and your talent as a
thief is truly genuine.
Thief Nora: Ehehe, thank you very much!

Phantom Thief Perno: It seems like my growing popularity is
preventing me from quitting as a phantom thief.

Phantom Thief Perno: Give me a little time... The final
return location will be the most challenging.

Phantom Thief Perno: I'll take some time to recover and
prepare myself.
Clea: Understood. Where can I accept the request?

Phantom Thief Perno: I'll let the final request take place
in [Oros]. With this, I'll be able to bring an end to
Phantom Thief Perno...

Phantom Thief Perno: I'll be able to report at my father's
grave...

Phoni the Phantom Thief: 'Once again, thank you all so much.
It's because all of you were here that I was able to bring
an end to Phoni the Phantom Thief.'
Clea: Is it really all over?

Phantom Thief Perno: 'The final rule for retiring as the
Phantom Thief Perno... is to remove and dispose of the
symbolic mask.'

Phantom Thief Perno: Is it alright to send the reward to the
guild at a later date? As a matter of family pride, I really
don't want to show my true face.

Phantom Thief Perno: It's a strange obsession to quit being
a phantom thief, but well...

Clea: There's no problem. I'm glad that the promise with my
father has been fulfilled.

Phantom Thief Perno: I wonder if the reason you all helped
me for free was because of that?
Clea: That might be true, but Perno-san really needed us.

Clea: I only reached out and grabbed it because you extended
your hand to me.

Phantom Thief Perno: Oh, you're such a good girl, ufufu. I
wouldn't want to introduce you to my wonderful husband

Phantom Thief Perno: I'm really grateful. It's just sad that
I can't go on adventures with everyone.

Farmer Lou: I have vague memories about this house... It
seems like it was an abandoned house... or maybe a family
used to live here...

Phantom Thief Perno: Today, I will be able to end my life as
a phantom thief. No, I will definitely put an end to the
Phantom Thief Perno.

Phantom Thief Perno: My father tried to do it alone, but I
have these girls... they're here for me.
Phantom Thief Perno: I'm going now, Father...
Housewife Shino: Yes, can I help you with something?
Clea: ...No, my friend used to live here.

Housewife Shino: Oh, is that so? It would be nice if you
could meet your friend again.
Farmer Lou: Shino, is there a customer?

Housewife Shino: It seems like there was a misunderstanding.
Your friend used to live here, it seems.
Clea: I apologize for the misunderstanding, then.
